{
  "stem": "13471.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Well, laughter, at that point-- absolutely impossible.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It could not be, you see.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I knew that the people who were laughing, were-- many of them were listening in English, you see.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So I put on my headphone.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I could hear this fellow, 'blasphemy, indecency, blasphemy, indecency,' you see, and then, on the Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Now what would happen was this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Virginia, in her nice, Midwestern, female voice would say everything up to the obscenities.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Then she would hand her microphone to the guy sitting next to her, who was a Lieutenant Colonel McIntosh in the British army, very Scottish, ready to do French into English, but that wasn't being used at the moment-- but who understood German just as well as he understood French.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he would give, [LAUGHS] in his Scottish accent, all these filthy, blasphemous expletives and hand the microphone back to her.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so you would get this back and forth between attractive female Midwestern American and this base of Scottish.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, of course, it's-- it's-- the unannounced alternation is funny.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But [? it was ?] beside the point.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Interpretation is supposed to be barely noticeable.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's not supposed to interfere with what's going on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this had turned into-- it turned it into a sideshow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And this we couldn't have.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I had to take Virginia out and put another [LAUGHS] interpreter in.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Now, you've told us, obviously, that, that these interpreters were servants of the court.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Tell us what court you mean.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The court was the International Military Tribunal, set up according to two different international treaties worked out in Paris before the end of the war, or just at the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
